➤ Open the AWS Management Console and sign in with the root or admin account.

➤ Go to IAM → Users → Add User.

➤ Enter a username (example: student-user).

➤ Enable AWS Management Console access and set a custom password.

➤ Click Next: Permissions.

➤ Choose Attach existing policies directly.

➤ Select the following policies:
• AmazonS3FullAccess
• AmazonEC2ReadOnlyAccess

➤ Click Create User to finish user creation.

⭐ Demonstrate Role-Based Access

➤ Copy the IAM login URL generated after user creation.

➤ Open a new browser or incognito window and log in using the IAM user credentials.

Access Verification:

✔ S3 Access:
The user can create buckets, upload objects, and delete files (Full Access).

✔ EC2 Access:
The user can only view EC2 instances but cannot start, stop, or terminate them (Read-Only Access).
